<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well....I've read every post here and I have a few comments for all of you.  I can count the days I have NOT played this game on ONE hand since LAST year.  Also, I AM a paladin, unlike some of you that have NO CLUE as to what life as a Paladin is like.  <BR>
<BR>
That having been said, one word to the warriors.  If you want our sword...then start a Paladin and delete your Warrior.  Please quit you damn crying.  Paladins are a mixed breed, we can't fight as well as Warriors and we can't heal etc as well as a Cleric.  So, why do you complain about a sword that most Paladins will never see anyway.  Go get yourselves a couple of nice weapons and shut up.  It's really upsetting to read all of this stuff from you guys that don't know what the hell you're talking about.  WHEW...take a breath<BR>
<BR>
I don't see why you don't just put all of this pent up energy into the game...go roleplay.  Quit worrying about our weapons and worry about your own.  I think you may be a little jealous because it looks SO FREAKIN COOL.  Like I said, if you want one...PLAY A PALADIN.  It's fun and thats the way its meant to be.  BTW....to the pally that said it was too late for a SF and was in his 20s...I just obtained mine a few days ago at level 35.  It took every bit of it too.  So you see...we have it harder obtaining our weapons...they don't think about that!! <BR>
<BR>
And now I would like to apologize to the rest of you for unleashing all of this anger.  But someone needed to tell these guys whats its like to be a Pally...and I know this won't do any good.  You Paladins need to stick up for yourselves.  Life is good as a Pally...we are here on Norrath to do good.  Be honorable.  Damn, I'm preaching again.  <BR>
<BR>
Well, don't listen to the whiners and keep your heads up!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Victus Silvercrest <BR>
Paladin of the 36th Circle<BR>
Tarew Marr<BR>
